{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17631599","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17631599"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:30:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:30:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17386"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17386","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17386"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.21,0.04,0.54,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10076"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75491"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10076"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17386"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61001"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5764"},{"type":"tags","id":"7811"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23583"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23585"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75491","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75491"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA research team is preparing patient data from a clinical trial for sharing with external collaborators. The dataset contains medical records, test results, demographic information, and contact details.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate method for maintaining patient confidentiality in shared research data?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Maintain full records but require signed confidentiality agreements","Replace patient names with sequential numbers only","Keep all original data but restrict access with passwords","Remove or encode all protected health information","Remove only names and addresses while keeping other identifiers"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eremove or encode all protected health information\u003C/strong\u003E. This includes names, dates of birth, addresses, phone numbers, email addresses, medical record numbers, health insurance numbers, biometric identifiers, and any other unique identifying characteristics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are inadequate:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERemove only names and addresses while keeping other identifiers\u003C/strong\u003E - This leaves too many potential identifiers that could be used to re-identify individuals\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKeep all original data but restrict access with passwords\u003C/strong\u003E - Access controls alone do not adequately protect confidentiality if the data contains identifiers\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReplace patient names with sequential numbers only\u003C/strong\u003E - This leaves other identifying information that could be used to re-identify individuals\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaintain full records but require signed confidentiality agreements\u003C/strong\u003E - Legal agreements do not prevent the possibility of identification from complete records\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProper de-identification may use techniques like anonymisation (permanent removal of identifiers) or pseudonymisation (reversible encoding of identifiers). The goal is to make it impossible or extremely difficult to link the data back to specific individuals while maintaining the scientific utility of the dataset.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Data confidentiality requires removing or encoding identifying information before sharing medical data.","Protected health information includes names, dates, addresses, contact details, identification numbers, and biometric data.","De-identification techniques include anonymisation (permanent removal) and pseudonymisation (reversible encoding)."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61001"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17386"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61001","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61001"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T21:20:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T00:54:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10076"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75491"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","li